  "title": "Resident Technical Officer (Architectural)",
  "description": "<p>Primary Responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Supervise and manage all architectural activities within the assigned projects.</li>\n  <li>Ensure that construction operations align with design specifications and regulatory requirements.</li>\n  <li>Analyze architectural drawings and document any necessary engineering adjustments.</li>\n  <li>Engage in collaborative efforts with architectural consultants to maintain project integrity.</li>\n  <li>Perform site inspections and evaluate project samples to ensure quality and compliance.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Qualifications:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>A recognized qualification in building or architectural disciplines.</li>\n  <li>Valid registration as a Resident Technical Officer (RTO) with IES/ACES.</li>\n  <li>Experience with projects related to the Land Transport Authority (LTA) is preferred.</li>\n  <li>Understanding of Building Information Modeling (BIM) for effective design coordination is advantageous.</li>\n  <li>At least two years of relevant experience in a similar RTO capacity.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If interested, please submit your application to cvs@jdawms.com with your expected salary and resume.</p>\n<p>We regret that only short-listed candidates will be contacted shortly. By submitting your application or resume, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and sharing of your personal information with potential employers for their assessment.</p>\n<p>JDA WMS Pte Ltd | EA Personnel: Pham Thi Tuyet Mai</p>\n<p>EA License No: 23S1595 | EA Registration No: R25127838</p>",
